We recommended that Management:

Require the concerned employee of the Municipality to submit the necessary lacking and relevant documents to establish the validity in the payment of 50% or more of  the monetized leave credits as provided for under Section 23 of the Omnibus Rules on Leave and  Section 5.14 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012, as follows: For monetization of 50% or more: Clinical abstract/medical procedures to be undertaken in case of health, medical and hospital needs; Barangay certification in case of need for financial assistance brought about by calamities, typhoon, fire, etc; and Other appropriate documents supporting the educational needs, extreme financial needs and other justifiable reasons for the monetization listed under Section 23 on the Omnibus Rules on leave of the CSC;

Direct the Human Resource Management Officer (HRMO) to make the necessary correction on the leave records of employees whose monetization were deducted from the sick leave credits by exhausting first their vacation leave credits;

Direct the HRMO to review all the leave records of all employees, including the elected officials of the Municipality and make the necessary adjustments caused by over or under-recording of earned leave credits, and miscalculation of the same; and 

- Henceforth, strictly observe and implement the rules and regulations as provided for under Rule XVI of the Omnibus Rules Implementing Book V of Executive Order No. 292 and CSC-DBM Joint Circular   No. 2-97 dated June 25, 1997, and ensure that all the required supporting documents will be duly attached to the claims.

